# Glossary of R objects

| Object | Type | Definition |
|--------|------|-----------|
| `stages` | character vector ($s$) | Names of the $s$ life-history stages, in order |
| `T_pop` | $s \times s$ matrix | Transition matrix $[u_{ji}]$: entry $(j,i)$ is the rate from stage $i$ to stage $j$ |
| `F_pop` | $s \times s$ matrix | Fecundity matrix: row 1 contains $F_i$, all other entries 0 |
| `A_pop` | $s \times s$ matrix | Full projection matrix $\mathbf{A} = \mathbf{T} + \mathbf{F}$ |
| `D_obs` | numeric vector ($s$) | Observed stage fractions; $\sum_i D_i = 1$ |
| `D_exp` | numeric vector ($s$) | Expected (equilibrium) stage fractions |
| `u_dot` | numeric vector ($s$) | $u_{\cdot i} = \sum_j u_{ji}$: total annual survival per stage |
| `over_u2` | scalar | $\overline{u^2} = \sum_i D_i\,u_{\cdot i}^2$: stage-weighted mean of squared survivals (used in Eq. 10, 11) |
| `r_i` | numeric vector ($s$) | $r_i = F_i\,D_i$: newborn contribution per stage |
| `L` | scalar | Generation time (years): stable-stage-weighted mean age of reproduction via $\mathbf{T}^x$ iteration, $x = 1\ldots500$ |
| `Ny_over_N` | scalar | Annual effective size ratio $= 1/(1-overline{u^2})$ (Eq. 11) |
| `Ne_over_N` | scalar | Generation-time effective size ratio $\approx 1/[(1-\bar{u})L]$ (Eq. 10) |
| `Min_N` | scalar | Minimum $N$ for $N_e \geq 5000$: $= 5000 / (N_e/N)$ |

### Worked numerical example: computing $\bar{u}$ for Miz

For population Miz the observed stage fractions are
$D_\text{obs} = (0.935, 0.038, 0.027)$ and the column-sum survivals
from the transition matrix are $u_{\cdot} = (0.797, 1.000, 1.000)$. Then:

$$
\bar{u}_\text{Miz}
= 0.935 \times 0.797 + 0.038 \times 1.000 + 0.027 \times 1.000
= 0.7452 + 0.0380 + 0.0270 = 0.8102
$$

The code below uses the transition matrix column sums directly, which avoids
rounding in the published table and produces the paper's reported values exactly.

